      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/229/1",
      "text": [
        ": أَکْثِرُوا مِنْ قِرَاءَهِ سَأَلَ سَائِلٌ فَإِنَّ مَنْ أَکْثَرَ قِرَاءَتَهَا لَمْ یَسْأَلْهُ اللَّهُ تَعَالَی یَوْمَ الْقِیَامَهِ عَنْ ذَنْبٍ عَمِلَهُ وَ أَسْکَنَهُ الْجَنَّهَ مَعَ مُحَمَّدٍ ص إِنْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from Muhammad b. Miskeen from ’Amru b. Shimr from Jabir from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: You people should recite “Sa’ala Saa-elun” (Surah Ma’arij) very much, because whoever recites Surah Ma’arij very much Allah would not count his mistakes on the Day of Judgment, and that man would be in Paradise with the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.s.), if Allah wills."
        ]
      }
